    <string name="power_on_startup_info">When enabled, the radio will automatically turn on when the app starts. Useful if you want the radio ready immediately.</string>
    <string name="show_debug_infos_info">Shows a debug overlay with RDS data (PS, PI, PTY, RT, RSSI, AF) for troubleshooting and development purposes.</string>
    <string name="loc_local_only_info">LOC (Local) mode filters out distant stations and only receives strong local signals. Enable this if you experience interference from far away stations.</string>
    <string name="mono_noise_reduction_info">Forces mono playback which reduces static noise on weak signals. Stereo requires stronger signals. Enable this for better audio quality on distant stations.</string>
    <string name="overwrite_favorites_info">When enabled, scanning will replace favorited stations if new data is found. When disabled, favorites are protected during scans.</string>
    <string name="rds_logging_info">Logs Radio Text (RT) changes to the archive. Each time the RT changes, a new entry is created with timestamp and all RDS data.</string>
    <string name="archive_retention_info">How long RDS archive entries are kept before automatic deletion. Older entries are removed on app start to save storage.</string>
